<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 24px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue'; font-weight: bold;">Glassfish  Installation on FreeBSD (v.11.0)</span></div><div>Note: Make sure that you have Java SDK (OpenSDK) installed.</div><div><br /></div><div>=&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;">cd</span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> /usr/ports/www/glassfish</span></div><div>=&gt; <span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">sudo</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">make install clean</span></div><div><br /></div><div>Edit the /etc/rc.conf and add the following:</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">glassfish_enable=“YES"</span></div><div><br /></div><div>To start the server: =&gt;</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">sudo </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0); font-weight: bold;">/usr/local/etc/rc.d/glassfish</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81); font-weight: bold;"> restart</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-style: italic;">Waiting for domain1 to start ....</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-style: italic;">Successfully started the domain : domain1</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-style: italic;">domain  Location: /usr/local/glassfish-4.1/glassfish/domains/domain1</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-style: italic;">Log File: /usr/local/glassfish-4.1/glassfish/domains/domain1/logs/server.log</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-style: italic;">Admin Port: 4848</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-style: italic;">Command start-domain executed successfully.</span></div><div><br /></div><div>Now you need to change the “admin” password ( default is empty):</div><div>=&gt; cd /usr/local/glassfish-4.1/bin</div><div>=&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;">./asadmin change-admin-password </span> &lt;Enter&gt;</div><div>    <span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">Enter admin user name [default: admin]&gt; &lt;Enter&gt; ( to keep the “admin”)</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">    </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">Enter the admin password&gt; &lt;Enter&gt;  ( the default password was empty)</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">    </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">Enter the new admin password&gt; H***3</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">    </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">Enter the new admin password again&gt; H***3</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">    </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">Command change-admin-password executed successfully.</span></div><div><br /></div><div>You also need the secret password for DAS ( Domain Administration Server):</div><div>=&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;">./asadmin --host localhost --port 4848 enable-secure-admin </span>&lt;Enter&gt;</div><div>    <span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">Enter admin user name&gt;  admin</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">    </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">Enter admin password for user "admin”&gt; H***3</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">    </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">You must restart all running servers for the change in secure admin to take effect.</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">    </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 33, 147);">Command enable-secure-admin executed successfully.</span></div><div><br /></div><div>Time to restart the server:</div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> sudo</span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0); font-weight: bold;"> /usr/local/etc/rc.d/glassfish</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81); font-weight: bold;"> restart</span></div><div><br /></div><div>The installation was tested for Glassfish 4.1 and no problems so far.</div><table title="" border="0"><colgroup><col /><col /></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap" align="left"><div>HTTP Port(s):</div></td><td><div>4848, 8080, 8181</div></td></tr></tbody></table><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div></en-note>